I really like underscores for two word variable names. It only becomes a problem when you have variable names which are overly long, and your eyes have to move further.<p><pre><code>     if(Accounts_Orders_Invoices_Table.Order_Invoice_Number == Order_Invoice_Number){ ...}    
     if(AccountsOrdersInvoicesTable.OrderInvoiceNumber == OrderInvoiceNumber){ ... }    
</code></pre>
But I don&#x27;t really care that much. I&#x27;ll just do whatever everyone else is doing. At least camcelCase keeps me from reaching for the _ as much and allows me to stay on the A-Za-z more of the time...
